headline.main: WELLES FINDS GERMANY NOT READY FOR A PEACE; Berlin Uses His Visit as Occasion for Putting Forth Nazi Hopes to Win Power in Victory Over British ENVOY SILENT BUT REICH TALKS

lead_paragraph: When Under-Secretary of State Summer Welles sailed for his European mission most students of the Old World situation expected that he would find small prospects of a successful peace move at this stage of the war. So far as Mr. Welles's experience in Berlin goes, there is every indication that such an expectation will be fulfilled.
